🟢 1. RELEVANCE (Most Important)

👉 Ask:

Does this insight help answer my objective?

Your objective:

State-wise COVID performance analysis
✔ Keep if:
Explains state performance
Explains trend over time
Explains recovery/death behavior
❌ Remove if:
Just obvious (e.g., “Maharashtra has high cases”)
Already covered by another insight
🔵 2. IMPACT

👉 Ask:

Is this insight significant or just minor?
✔ Keep if:
Large difference (big gap, strong trend)
Important month (April–June peak)
Major state (Maharashtra, Kerala)
❌ Remove if:
Small variation
Minor state change
“Normal behavior” insights
🟡 3. UNIQUENESS

👉 Ask:

Is this repeating something I already said?
Example:

❌ These are same:

“Maharashtra has highest confirmed”
“Maharashtra dominates confirmed cases”

👉 Keep only ONE

🧠 SIMPLE RULE (VERY IMPORTANT)
1 insight = 1 idea

👉 Don’t repeat same idea in different words

🔥 PRACTICAL METHOD (DO THIS)
Step 1: Group your insights

You already have:

Peaks
Trends
State comparison
Rates
Step 2: Pick TOP 1–2 from each group

👉 Example:

1 Peak insight
1 Trend insight
1 Comparison insight
1 Rate insight
Step 3: Limit to 5–6 insights MAX
Too many insights = confusion
Few strong insights = clarity
